HEADWORD: Topiarian
<hw>Top`i*a"ri*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Toplary</er>.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to the ornamental cutting
and trimming of trees, hedges, etc.; practicing ornamental
gardening.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧The <xex>topiarian</xex>
artist.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Sir W. Scott.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>All the pedantries of the <qex>topiarian</qex> art.</q>
<rj><qau>C. Kingsley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Topiary</ent>⟦br⟧
